news.title: Developers to meet Gujarat CM over increase in jantri rates
news.para: CREDAI Gujarat chairman Ajay Patel said, “We have decided to meet the chief minister and we will demand that relief should be given in purchasing FSI and NA premiums to ensure projects remain viable.”

news.title: Illegal borewells found at 16 more housing projects in Gautam Buddh Nagar
news.para: The move brings an end to the borewells investigation. In the first phase, the committee, comprising the Noida district magistrate and the state and central pollution control board officials, examined 33 projects and found illegal borewells at 25 sites. In total, it has investigated 63 projects of 40 builders.

news.title: Mumbai: 25 years on, two builders get two-year rigorous imprisonment for cheating buyer
news.para: Refusing leniency to builders Harun Umatiya and Moiddiin Umatiya who have been convicted of cheating a flat buyer of Rs 4.5 lakh in 1998, metropolitan magistrate Nilesh V Bansal said the accused knew that sale deed cannot be registered unless valid permission is obtained from municipal authorities.
